        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(hooks): wire message:sending internal hook to user-defined hooks",
        "body": "## Problem\nThe `message:sending` internal hook was not wired to user-defined hooks, so hook authors could not intercept or modify outgoing messages before delivery.\n\n## Fix\nAdd a `message:sending` internal hook bridge with underscore event-key dispatch (`message_sending`), wire it into the outbound delivery path, and update tests.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` (+24 -2): Add `message:sending` event bridge\n- `src/hooks/internal-hooks.test.ts` (+14): Test coverage\n- `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts` (+27): Wire hook into delivery\n- `src/infra/outbound/deliver.test.ts` (+48 -62): Update tests\n- `src/infra/heartbeat-runner.ts` (+13 -1): Heartbeat hook suppression\n- `src/infra/heartbeat-runner.tool-response.test.ts` (+27): Heartbeat test\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/hooks/internal-hooks.test.ts (14 tests)\n✓ src/infra/heartbeat-runner.tool-response.test.ts (98 tests)\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  112 passed (112)\n```\n\n### Behavior addressed\n`message:sending` hook now fires for user-defined hooks before outbound delivery.\n\n### Evidence after fix\nAll 112 related tests pass, including hook firing, event-key dispatch, and heartbeat suppression.\n",
